## Next.js Best Practices

### App Router & Server Components
- Use Server Components by default; mark Client Components with `"use client"`
- Leverage `async/await` in Server Components for data fetching
- Use `generateMetadata` for dynamic SEO metadata
- Implement `loading.js` and `error.js` for every route segment
- Streaming with `Suspense` boundaries for progressive rendering

### Client Components
- Minimal `"use client"` usage - only when interactivity needed
- Use React 19 hooks: `useActionState`, `useFormStatus`, `useOptimistic`
- Server Actions for mutations (no separate API routes needed)
- `useTransition` for non-urgent state updates

## TypeScript Best Practices
- `strict: true` in `tsconfig.json`
- Avoid `any`; use `unknown` for untyped data
- Server Actions must be `async` functions
- Explicit return types for React components (`React.FC<Props>`)

